"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The hue parameter in sns.scatterplot is expected to be either categorical or numeric. However, when it is numeric, color mapping will behave differently. In this case, 'color' is numeric but a list of colors is provided for the palette, which is typically used for categorical variables. This may lead to unexpected color mapping behavior.\", \"patch\": \"11,12c11\\n< colors = ['#747FE3', '#8EE35D', '#E37346']\\n< sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='x', y='y', hue='color', legend=False, palette=colors, s=50)\\n---\\n> sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='x', y='y', hue='color', legend=False, cmap='viridis', s=50)\\n\"}"